  "prompt": "What is a \"point\" in loan-sharking slang?",
  "response": "In loan-sharking slang, a \"point\" refers to one percentage point of interest charged on a loan. For example, if a loan shark says they are charging \"five points,\" it means they are charging 5% interest on the loan. Loan sharks often charge extremely high interest rates, well above legal limits, and use intimidation or threats to ensure repayment.",
